      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "plus more to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "black pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon",
      "notes": "ground"
    },
    {
      "name": "fresh cilantro",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "in a large mixing bowl, combine fermented corn flour and 2 cups of water, stirring until smooth",
    "bring the mixture to a boil in a large saucepan, then reduce the heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes",
    "stir in sherry vinegar, salt, and black pepper",
    "add diced sweet potatoes and cook for 5 minutes more",
    "in a separate pan, heat coconut oil over medium heat and sauté thinly sliced red onion and minced garlic until softened",
    "stir in chopped spinach and cook until wilted",
    "to assemble the bowls, place a scoop of cooked ugali in each bowl, top with sautéed onion and spinach mixture, and garnish with chopped cilantro",
    "season with additional salt and pepper to taste"
  ],
